3870 // pattern.
3871 static bool isSafeToRemoveBitCeilSelect(ICmpInst::Predicate Pred, Value *Cond0,
3872                                         const APInt *Cond1, Value *CtlzOp,
3873                                         unsigned BitWidth,
3874                                         bool &ShouldDropNoWrap) {
3875   // The challenge in recognizing std::bit_ceil(X) is that the operand is used
3876   // for the CTLZ proper and select condition, each possibly with some
3877   // operation like add and sub.
3878   //
3879   // Our aim is to make sure that -ctlz & (BitWidth - 1) == 0 even when the
3880   // select instruction would select 1, which allows us to get rid of the select
3881   // instruction.
3882   //
3883   // To see if we can do so, we do some symbolic execution with ConstantRange.
3884   // Specifically, we compute the range of values that Cond0 could take when
3885   // Cond == false.  Then we successively transform the range until we obtain
3886   // the range of values that CtlzOp could take.
3887   //
3888   // Conceptually, we follow the def-use chain backward from Cond0 while
3889   // transforming the range for Cond0 until we meet the common ancestor of Cond0
3890   // and CtlzOp.  Then we follow the def-use chain forward until we obtain the
3891   // range for CtlzOp.  That said, we only follow at most one ancestor from
3892   // Cond0.  Likewise, we only follow at most one ancestor from CtrlOp.
